    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dealing-with-squatters-in-your-home"/>
    <title>Dealing with squatters in your home</title>
    <category>Publication</category>
    <summary>Guidance for property owners about the new criminal offence of squatting and about how to regain possession of their properties.</summary>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;From 1 September 2012, a person squatting in a residential building is committing a crime. The offence covers squatting in all residential buildings. It protects homeowners and lawful occupiers who discover squatters have occupied their homes. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This guidance is jointly produced by the Department for Communities and Local Government and the Ministry of Justice. It is aimed at informing property owners about the new offence and the procedures for regaining possession of their properties from squatters.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It updates the version published on 21 March 2011.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
